race.comment: Hayes-trained TARPAULIN (8) was heavily bet to win a 70 at Horsham and was just nutted. His effort three back at Flemington in this grade reads well, and he gets his chance in this lineup. Wary of stablemate LEGIO TEN (4), who needed the run first-up after a stable switch from the Bedggood yard. He's up to this at best and is proven second-up. Has the blinkers on again and the in-form Nash Rawiller is a key jockey engagement. Keep a close eye on the late betting moves. PRECIOUS CHARM (3) resumes for Simon Wilde. Will come into his own over longer distances but has won 2/4 fresh at 1200m. Can't be taken lightly. GEORGIE GET MAD (5) resumes and also has good ability. His two Flemington jumpouts suggest he'll be presented forward and Riordan sticks from those.
